      <byline class="print_byline">By Salman Masood (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Masood, Salman</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Appeals Court convenes in Karachi, Pakistan, to hear case of Ahmed Omar Sheikh, British born Iislamic militant convicted of masterminding Wall Street Journal reporter Daniel Pearl's January 2002 kidnapping and murder; Sheikh was given death sentence during earlier trial (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A court in the southern port city of Karachi began hearing an appeal by Ahmed Omar Sheikh, the British born Islamic militant who was convicted of masterminding the kidnapping and killing in January 2002 of Daniel Pearl, an American reporter. Mr. Sheikh was found guilty and sentenced to death in July 2002, and he appealed the conviction almost immediately. Three other Islamic militants have also appealed their life sentences in the same case.</p>
        <p>Salman Masood (NYT)</p>
      </block>
